$lang['The hexadecimal system is a base 16 number notation, while the decimal system is a base 10 number notation. In other words, the hexadecimal system uses 16 symbols to represent numbers, while the decimal system uses 10 symbols. This expansion also allows for a higher information density-hexadecimal digits can represent twice as many values as decimal digits.'] = 'Hexadecimal nhyehyɛe no yɛ nnyinaso 16 nɔma nkyerɛwde, bere a decimal nhyehyɛe no yɛ nnyinaso 10 nɔma nkyerɛwde. Ɔkwan foforo so no, hexadecimal nhyehyɛe no de agyiraehyɛde 16 na egyina hɔ ma akontaahyɛde, bere a decimal nhyehyɛe no de agyiraehyɛde 10 na edi dwuma. Saa ntrɛwmu yi nso ma kwan ma wonya nsɛm density a ɛkorɔn-hexadecimal digits betumi agyina hɔ ama values ​​a ɛboro decimal digits mmɔho abien.';
$lang['Hexadecimal numbers are made up of 16 digits instead of the 10 in a decimal number. The order of these numbers starts over after F (or 15 in decimal), while it doesn’t in the decimals. Check out the table below to see how they compare!'] = 'Wɔde digit 16 na ɛyɛ hexadecimal nɔma sen sɛ ɛbɛyɛ 10 a ɛwɔ decimal nɔma mu. Sɛnea akontaahyɛde ahorow yi hyehyɛ no fi ase bio wɔ F akyi (anaasɛ 15 wɔ decimal mu), bere a ɛnte saa wɔ decimal mu. Hwɛ pon a ɛwɔ aseɛ ha no na hwɛ sɛdeɛ wɔde toto ho!';
$lang['How do you convert a Hexadecimal to a Decimal?'] = 'Wobɛyɛ dɛn adan Hexadecimal ayɛ no Decimal?';
$lang['When converting hexadecimal to decimal, the first step is to divide the hex number by 16. This will give you the base number. The second step is to divide each digit of the hex number by 16 and write down the results. Finally, add up all of the numbers that were just calculated.'] = 'Sɛ woredan hexadecimal akɔ decimal a, ade a edi kan ne sɛ wobɛkyekyɛ hex nɔma no mu 16. Eyi bɛma woanya nnyinaso nɔma no. Ade a ɛto so abien ne sɛ wobɛkyekyɛ hex nɔma no mu akontaahyɛde biara mu 16 na woakyerɛw nea ebefi mu aba no. Awiei koraa no, fa akontaahyɛde ahorow a wobuu ho akontaa nkyɛe no nyinaa bom.';
$lang['For example, if someone wants to convert 9F7A to decimal, they would first divide 9F7A by 16 which equals 6051. Then they would divide each digit of 6051 by 16 which equals 381. Lastly, they would add up 381 + 381 + 381 which equals 1144. Therefore, 9F7A in decimal is equal to 1144'] = 'Sɛ nhwɛso no, sɛ obi pɛ sɛ ɔdan 9F7A kɔ decimal a, anka obedi kan akyekyɛ 9F7A mu 16 a ɛne 6051 yɛ pɛ.Afei wɔbɛkyekyɛ 6051 digit biara mu 16 a ɛne 381 yɛ pɛ.Nea etwa to no, wɔbɛka 381 + 381 + 381 a ɛyɛ pɛ 1144. Enti, 9F7A a ɛwɔ decimal mu no ne 1144 yɛ pɛ';
$lang['How do you convert a Decimal to a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Wobɛyɛ dɛn adan Decimal ayɛ no Hexadecimal?';
$lang['Converting decimal to hexadecimal is a simple process, and can be done with a calculator or online converter. In order to convert the number, divide it by 16 and take the remainder. This remainder will then correspond to a hexadecimal digit. For example, if you have the decimal number 234, divide it by 16 and take the remainder: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Therefore, in hexadecimal notation, this number would be written as “E2”.'] = 'Decimal a wɔdannan no kɔ hexadecimal mu no yɛ adeyɛ a ɛnyɛ den, na wobetumi de calculator anaa online converter ayɛ. Sɛnea ɛbɛyɛ a wobɛdan akontaahyɛde no, kyekyɛ mu 16 na fa nea aka no. Afei saa nkaeɛ yi ne hexadecimal digit bɛyɛ pɛ. Sɛ nhwɛso no, sɛ wowɔ decimal nɔma 234 a, kyekyɛ mu 16 na fa nea aka no: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Enti, wɔ hexadecimal nkyerɛwde mu no, anka wɔbɛkyerɛw saa nɔma yi sɛ “E2”.';
$lang['There are many tools available online that can help with converting between decimal and hexadecimal numbers. Additionally, most calculators have a built-in function that will allow you to do this conversion very easily. With just a few clicks of the mouse or taps on the keyboard, you’ll be able to change any decimal value into its corresponding hexadecimal equivalent!'] = 'Nnwinnade pii wɔ intanɛt so a ebetumi aboa ma wɔadan decimal ne hexadecimal nɔma ntam. Bio nso, calculator dodow no ara wɔ adwuma bi a wɔde ahyɛ mu a ɛbɛma woatumi ayɛ saa nsakrae yi mmerɛw yiye. Sɛ wobɔ mouse no so kakraa bi anaasɛ wobɔ keyboard no so a, wubetumi asesa decimal bo biara akɔ ne hexadecimal a ɛne no sɛ no so!';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Hexadecimal over a Decimal?'] = 'Mfaso bɛn na ɛwɔ so sɛ wode Hexadecimal bedi dwuma sen Decimal?';
$lang['The hexadecimal, or base-16, system was designed to emulate some of the same properties as the decimal system. In other words, it was created to make things easier for us humans. The number 423 has 16 digits instead of 10 digits available in a decimal system. This is because hexadecimal uses a base of 16 symbols instead of 10. After F, the order begins again with 0 and so on and so forth until we get to 15 which is notated as F.'] = 'Wɔyɛɛ hexadecimal, anaa base-16, nhyehyɛe no sɛnea ɛbɛyɛ a ebesuasua nneɛma koro no ara bi a ɛwɔ decimal nhyehyɛe no mu. Ɔkwan foforo so no, wɔbɔɔ no sɛnea ɛbɛyɛ a nneɛma bɛyɛ mmerɛw ama yɛn a yɛyɛ nnipa. Nnɔmba 423 no wɔ nkyerɛwde 16 sen sɛ ɛbɛyɛ akontaahyɛde 10 a ɛwɔ decimal nhyehyɛe mu. Eyi te saa efisɛ hexadecimal de nnyinaso a ɛwɔ sɛnkyerɛnnede 16 di dwuma sen sɛ ɛde 10. F akyi no, nhyehyɛe no san fi ase bio de 0 ne nea ɛkeka ho ne nea ɛkeka ho kosi sɛ yebedu 15 a wɔakyerɛw so sɛ F.';
$lang['Hexadecimal encoding reduces the number of digits by a factor of eight when compared to the decimal system. Additionally, hexadecimal numbers have an information density that is twice as high as decimal numbers do. So, why should you bother learning this funky little numbering scheme? Because it can make your life easier! When working with digital systems or data transmission, using hex will save you time and energy when decoding cryptic messages or data streams.'] = 'Hexadecimal encoding ma digit dodow so tew mpɛn awotwe bere a wɔde toto decimal nhyehyɛe no ho no. Bio nso, hexadecimal nɔma wɔ nsɛm a ɛyɛ den a ɛboro decimal nɔma so mmɔho abien. Enti, dɛn nti na ɛsɛ sɛ wohaw wo ho sɛ wubesua saa nɔma nhyehyɛe ketewaa a ɛyɛ funky yi? Efisɛ ebetumi ama w’asetra ayɛ mmerɛw! Sɛ wode dijitaal nhyehyɛe anaa data a wɔde mena reyɛ adwuma a, hex a wode bedi dwuma no bɛma woakora bere ne w’ahoɔden so bere a worekyerɛkyerɛ nkrasɛm a ɛyɛ ahintasɛm anaa data nsu mu no.';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Decimal over a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Mfaso bɛn na ɛwɔ so sɛ wode Decimal bedi dwuma sen Hexadecimal?';
$lang['When it comes to binary coding, Hexadecimal is more efficient because it reduces 8 digits to 2. Additionally, Hex provides a greater degree of information density and higher accuracy in numbers than binary does. This is due to the fact that Hex uses 16 symbols instead of just two like binary. Because of this increased efficiency, Hexadecimal is often used when binary coding in computing and digital electronics as well as for computer science applications.'] = 'Sɛ ɛba binary coding so a, Hexadecimal yɛ adwuma yie ɛfiri sɛ ɛtew digit 8 so kɔ 2. Bio nso, Hex ma nsɛm a ɛyɛ den kɛseɛ ne dodoɔ a ɛyɛ pɛpɛɛpɛ wɔ dodoɔ mu sene binary. Eyi fi nokwasɛm a ɛyɛ sɛ Hex de nsɛnkyerɛnne 16 di dwuma sen sɛ ɔde abien pɛ bedi dwuma te sɛ binary. Esiane sɛ ɛyɛ adwuma yiye a ɛkɔ soro yi nti, wɔtaa de Hexadecimal di dwuma bere a wɔde binary coding di dwuma wɔ kɔmputa ne dijitaal ɛlɛtrɔnik mfiri mu ne kɔmputa ho nyansahu mu dwumadie nso.';
$lang['In addition, Hexadecimal takes up less space than decimal. With only two digits instead of 8 binary digits, Hex numbers represent large numbers much more concisely. This can be very helpful when working with computer systems, as there is less chance for mistakes when typing in hex codes compared to decimal codes which have so many decimal points all over the place!'] = 'Bio nso, Hexadecimal gye baabi ketewaa bi sen decimal. Esiane sɛ Hex nɔma ahorow no yɛ akontaahyɛde abien pɛ sen sɛ ɛbɛyɛ akontaahyɛde abien 8 nti, egyina hɔ ma akontaahyɛde akɛse wɔ ɔkwan tiawa so kɛse. Eyi betumi aboa kɛse bere a wode kɔmputa nhyehyɛe reyɛ adwuma no, efisɛ hokwan kakraa bi na ɛwɔ hɔ sɛ mfomso bɛba bere a worekyerɛw hex koodu ahorow mu sɛ wɔde toto decimal koodu a ɛwɔ decimal nsɛntitiriw pii wɔ baabiara ho a!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Dɛn ne botae ahorow a wobetumi de Hexadecimal agyina hɔ ama no?';
$lang['A hexadecimal number is a number that uses 16 digits instead of the 10 digits we use in the decimal system. This number system is called base-16, and it helps us to emulate the properties of our familiar decimal system. In hexadecimal, each digit represents a power of 16. The numbers 0 through 9 represent the powers of 1 through 10, while A through F represent the powers of 11 through 15.'] = 'Hexadecimal nɔma yɛ nɔma a ɛde digit 16 di dwuma sen sɛ yɛde digit 10 a yɛde di dwuma wɔ decimal nhyehyɛe no mu no bedi dwuma. Wɔfrɛ saa nɔma nhyehyɛe yi base-16, na ɛboa yɛn ma yesuasua yɛn decimal nhyehyɛe a yenim no yiye no su. Wɔ hexadecimal mu no, digit biara gyina hɔ ma tumi a ɛyɛ 16. Akontaabu 0 kosi 9 gyina hɔ ma tumi a efi 1 kosi 10, bere a A kosi F gyina hɔ ma tumi a efi 11 kosi 15.';
$lang['Just like in decimal, after 16 symbols have been used in Hexadecimal, the order of numbers starts over again at zero. So, hexadecimal 10 is equal to decimal 16, and hexadecimal 11 is equal to decimal 17. And so on!'] = 'Sɛnea ɛte wɔ decimal mu no, bere a wɔde agyiraehyɛde ahorow 16 adi dwuma wɔ Hexadecimal mu akyi no, akontaahyɛde ahorow no fi ase bio wɔ zero. Enti, hexadecimal 10 ne decimal 16 yɛ pɛ, na hexadecimal 11 ne decimal 17 yɛ pɛ.Ne nea ɛkeka ho!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Decimal?'] = 'Dɛn ne botae ahorow a wobetumi de Decimal agyina hɔ ama no?';
$lang['The Decimal system starts with 10 and goes up to 15. This means that the range of values that can be represented by a decimal number is from 0-9, followed by A-F (10-15).'] = 'Decimal nhyehyeɛ no firi aseɛ firi 10 na ɛkɔ soro kɔsi 15. Wei kyerɛ sɛ nsusuiɛ dodoɔ a wɔbɛtumi de decimal nɔma agyina hɔ ama no firi 0-9, na AF (10-15) di akyire.';
$lang['How do you decode Hexadecimal?'] = 'Wobɛyɛ dɛn decode Hexadecimal ase?';
$lang['When it comes to decoding Hexadecimal, there are a few things you need to know. First, just like the decimal system, the hexadecimal system has 10 symbols (0-9) that represent numbers. However, in hexadecimal, these digits have values that are twice as large as their counterparts in the decimal system. So, while the number “10” is represented by the symbol “A” in hexadecimal, it would be equal to “10” in the decimal system.'] = 'Sɛ ɛba Hexadecimal decoding so a, nneɛma kakraa bi wɔ hɔ a ɛsɛ sɛ wuhu. Nea edi kan no, te sɛ decimal nhyehyɛe no ara pɛ no, hexadecimal nhyehyɛe no wɔ agyiraehyɛde ahorow 10 (0-9) a egyina hɔ ma akontaahyɛde ahorow. Nanso, wɔ hexadecimal mu no, saa digit ahorow yi wɔ values ​​a ɛboro wɔn mfɛfo a wɔwɔ decimal nhyehyɛe no mu no mmɔho abien. Enti, bere a wɔde agyiraehyɛde “A” gyina hɔ ma akontaahyɛde “10” wɔ hexadecimal mu no, anka ɛne “10” bɛyɛ pɛ wɔ decimal nhyehyɛe no mu.';
$lang['Similarly, after reaching 9 in Hexadecimal (represented by “F”), we start counting again at 10 (“10”). This pattern continues until we reach 15 (“1F”), at which point we reset back to 0 and begin counting again at 16 (“20”). This might sound confusing at first, but with a little practice, it will become second nature!'] = 'Saa ara nso na bere a yedu 9 wɔ Hexadecimal (a wɔde “F” gyina hɔ ma) mu akyi no, yefi ase kan bio wɔ 10 (“10”). Saa nhyehyɛe yi kɔ so kosi sɛ yebedu 15 (“1F”), na saa bere no yɛsan de kɔ 0 na yefi ase kan bio wɔ 16 (“20”). Ebia eyi bɛyɛ te sɛ nea ɛyɛ adwenem naayɛ mfiase no, nanso sɛ wode di dwuma kakra a, ɛbɛyɛ abɔde a ɛto so abien!';
$lang['Lastly, just like in base 10 (the decimal system), each place value of a hexadecimal number represents a power of 16. So for example, if we had the number 423004 stored as a hexadecimal value:'] = 'Nea etwa to no, te sɛ nea ɛwɔ base 10 (decimal nhyehyɛe no) mu no, beae bo biara a ɛwɔ hexadecimal nɔma mu no gyina hɔ ma tumi a ɛyɛ 16. Enti sɛ nhwɛso no, sɛ yɛwɔ nɔma 423004 a wɔde sie sɛ hexadecimal bo a:';
