$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Wubetumi de hexadecimal adi dwuma de adan decimal ne binary values ​​ntam. Sɛ nhwɛso no, sɛ wodan 10011011001010 kɔ hexadecimal mu a, ɛbɛma woanya 0x4F. Wei kyerε sε, botaeε 4F gyina hɔ ma binary nɔma 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Wɔ akontabuo ne kɔmputa ho nyansahu mu no, hexadecimal (a ɛsan nso yɛ base 16, anaa hex) yɛ gyinabea akontabuo nhyehyɛeɛ a ne radix, anaa base, yɛ 16. Ɛde nsɛnkyerɛnneɛ ahodoɔ dunum di dwuma, mpɛn pii no ɛyɛ nsɛnkyerɛnneɛ 0–9 de gyina hɔ ma gyinapɛn zero kɔsi akron, . ne A, B, C, D, E, F (anaasɛ ɔkwan foforo so a–f) de gyina hɔ ma gyinapɛn ahorow du kosi dunum. Sɛ nhwɛso no, hexadecimal nɔma 2AF3 yɛ pɛ, wɔ decimal mu, ne (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , anaa 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Hexadecimal digit biara gyina hɔ ma binary digits (bits) anan (a wɔsan frɛ no &quot;nibble&quot;), na hexadecimal nkyerɛwde a wɔde di dwuma titiriw ne sɛ nnipa adamfofa kwan so sɛnkyerɛnne a ɛkyerɛ binary coded values ​​wɔ kɔmputa ne dijitaal ɛlɛtrɔnik mu. Sɛ nhwɛsoɔ no, byte botaeɛ tumi firi 0 kɔsi 255 (decimal) nanso ɛbɛtumi akyerɛ no yie sɛ hexadecimal digit mmienu wɔ 00 kɔsi FF. Wɔtaa de hexadecimal nso gyina hɔ ma kɔmputa so memory address ahorow.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex yɛ Hexadecimal tiawa, a egyina base -16 nhyehyeɛ so na wɔde di dwuma de ma sɛdeɛ wɔgyina hɔ ma akwankyerɛ a wɔde kɔ kɔmputa so no yɛ mmerɛ. Wɔyɛɛ saa nkyerɛwde 16 nɔma nhyehyɛe yi sɛ ɔkwan a wɔfa so siw nɔma abien a ɛwɔ bit 8 ano, enti wobetumi de data ahyɛ kɔmputa mu a wɔmmɔ mmɔden biara. Wobetumi de hex digit ahorow abien akyerɛw na akyerɛw a hex digit biara kyerɛ nibble anaa ebia 4-bits format.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Saa nɔma nhyehyɛe yi de agyiraehyɛde ahorow 16 a wɔde gyina hɔ ma wɔ ɔkwan a efi 0-9 anaa AF so na edi dwuma. 0–9 no gyina hɔ ma akontabuo a ɛkɔsi akron berɛ a AF no gyina hɔ ma akontabuo 10–15. Sɛ wɔde toto akontaahyɛde nhyehyɛe ahorow abiɛsa a aka no ho a, wobu akontaahyɛde nhyehyɛe a ɛwɔ hexadecimal no sɛ ɛno ne nea etu mpɔn sen biara.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Wo hexadecimal koodu no nyɛ adwuma';
